<br>The <b>Common Admission Test (CAT)</b> is a common entrance exam for admission to most of major Indian business schools. It is conducted by the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) and is considered as one of the toughest entrance exams world wide. Apart from the Indian Institutes of Management (IIM) at Ahmedabad, Bangalore, Calcutta, Lucknow, Indore, Shillong and Kozhikode, over 100 other Management Institutes use the CAT for short listing candidates. 
<br>
<br>The exam is conducted once a year on the Third Sunday of November. Test is held in more than 20 cities around the country. Examinations centers are assigned to the candidates based on their preference. 
<br>
